      <para id="id44498400">Did you know?</para>
      <para id="id42492802">In the sum 77 ÷ 22 = 3,5, the ,5 shown on the calculator is <emphasis effect="bold">NOT</emphasis> the remainder but actually a decimal fraction!</para>
      <para id="id44207585">,5 = 5 tenths</para>
      <para id="id44207594">77 ÷ 22 = 3 rem 11</para>
      <list id="id44218578" list-type="bulleted">
        <item>Can you see that ,5 is not equal to 11, but </item>
      </list>
      <para id="id44240115">to 0,5 of 22, which is 11?</para>
      <para id="id44240119">BRAIN-TEASER!</para>
      <list id="id44240124" list-type="bulleted">
